We are going to create a list of unique XSS payloads that attempt to bypass WAFs, CSP, and other security measures by using various obfuscation, encoding, and uncommon techniques. Note: These are for educational purposes and should only be used in environments where you have explicit permission to test.

The payloads will use a mix of:

    Multiple encoding layers (base64, hex, URL encoding, etc.)

    JavaScript features (template strings, regex, ES6 syntax, etc.)

    HTML entities and event handlers

    CSS and SVG vectors

    Dynamic code evaluation (eval, Function, setTimeout, etc.)

    Bypass common WAF regex patterns

